title: Groton denies Notre Dame's bid to clinch
text:
Groton denies Notre Dame's bid to clinch Andrew Legare, alegare@stargazette.com | @SGAndrewLegare 10:28 p.m. EDT October 9, 2015 Four touchdowns from junior running back Matt Gombas helped carry Indians to a 35-14 victory Buy Photo Crusader Derrick Stark targets the end zone while fighting through Groton Indian players Friday. (Photo: KELLY GAMPEL / Staff Photo) Buy Photo 15 CONNECT 6 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
SOUTHPORT — Four touchdowns from junior running back Matt Gombas and a dominant defensive effort in the second half helped carry Groton to a 35-14 victory over Elmira Notre Dame on Friday night, denying the Crusaders’ bid to wrap up the Section 4 Football Conference, Division VIII title. 
Gombas finished with 128 yards and three touchdowns on 21 carries. He also caught a 57-yard touchdown on a screen play that helped give the Indians the lead for good, 15-14, early in the second quarter. 
Groton (4-2 overall) completed the Division VIII portion of its schedule at 3-1. Notre Dame (4-2) dropped to 2-1 in the division, with a game remaining next Saturday at Newfield. Moravia is also 2-1 with a division game left against Spencer-Van Etten. 
The division champion would be decided on a tiebreaker if all three teams finish at 3-1. Groton’s only division loss came to Moravia, which lost to Notre Dame. The top two teams in each of the Class D divisions in Section 4 qualify for the quarterfinals, with two others advancing as wild cards. 
Derrick Stark scored both Crusaders touchdowns, the first on a 2-yard run that gave them an 8-7 lead in the first quarter, with Iman McKay adding a two-point run. Stark’s 5-yard scoring run put Notre Dame up 14-7 less than a minute into the second quarter. Buy Photo The Notre Dame Crusaders took on the Groton Indians Friday night on the Crusader's field. KELLY GAMPEL / Staff Photo
